---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Apps for Agency-Managed Stores in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for agency-managed stores by permissions, repeatable workflows, reporting, pricing context, source links, and implementation tradeoffs.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Agencies managing complex lifecycle programs','Deep events, segments, and reusable flow logic','Governance and account costs need careful control','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Retail agencies launching email and SMS quickly','Accessible multichannel automation','Client-specific edge cases need documentation','https://www.omnisend.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Sequenzy','Small agencies standardizing email sequences','Focused workflows and low operational overhead','May lack enterprise agency controls','https://sequenzy.io/'],['Brevo','Agencies supporting marketing and transactional email','Broad channel coverage and contact options','More manual ecommerce modeling','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Drip','DTC agencies reporting on repeat purchase','Commerce automation and revenue context','Less suitable for non-commerce clients','https://www.drip.com/features']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">An agency’s email platform must be repeatable without becoming generic. Permissions, naming conventions, QA, reporting, and client ownership matter as much as the number of automations a tool can create.</p><p>We prioritize reusable operating patterns, account separation, review workflows, and defensible reporting. Confirm current pricing, seats, and client-account terms from official sources before standardizing a stack.</p><h2>Shortlist for agencies</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>First workflow</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[0]==='Klaviyo'?'Reusable lifecycle framework':a[0]==='Omnisend'?'Retail campaign template':a[0]==='Sequenzy'?'Client onboarding sequence':a[0]==='Brevo'?'Standard transactional handoff':'Retention reporting playbook'}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for agency-managed stores</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[0]} is valuable when the agency can keep client data, approvals, access, and reporting distinct. A reusable framework should define what changes by client—catalog, audience, consent, offer, and brand voice—rather than copying every trigger unchanged.</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[2]}. Start with a documented onboarding, QA checklist, and one reporting template. Evaluate time-to-launch, error rate, client approval cycles, and cohort outcomes instead of presenting an unsupported average revenue claim.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}; supports repeatable client delivery; can use Shopify signals.</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}; seats, accounts, and contact volume affect total cost.</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Verify official pricing for contacts, sends, seats, permissions, and SMS.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Agency priority</th><th>Start with</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Complex lifecycle delivery</td><td>Klaviyo</td><td>Deep event and segment controls.</td></tr><tr><td>Lean standardized sequences</td><td>Sequenzy</td><td>Focused operations can simplify delivery.</td></tr><tr><td>Commerce retention reporting</td><td>Drip</td><td>Good fit for DTC client cohorts.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>See the <a href="/shopify-email">Shopify email overview</a>, <a href="/alternatives">alternatives library</a>, and <a href="/guides/implementation-plan">implementation guide</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
